  "prompt": "How do I get bank account details from account number in SBI?",
  "response": "It's generally not possible or legal to obtain the full bank account details, such as the account holder's personal information or the bank balance, solely from the account number. Banks, including State Bank of India (SBI), have strict privacy policies and regulations to protect their customers' information.\n\nHowever, if you are the account holder and need access to your own account details, you can proceed with the following steps:\n\n1. **Online Banking:**\n   - Log in to the SBI online banking portal using your credentials (username and password).\n   - Navigate to the account summary or detailed statement section to find your account details.\n\n2. **Mobile Banking:**\n   - Download and set up the SBI mobile app.\n   - Log in using your credentials.\n   - Access your account information from the dashboard.\n\n3. **Visit a Branch:**\n   - Go to your nearest SBI branch with valid identification documents.\n   - Request the bank staff to provide your account details.\n\n4. **Customer Support:**\n   - Call the SBI customer care number and verify your identity over the phone.\n   - Ask for the information you need from your account.\n\n5. **ATM:**\n   - Use an SBI ATM to check your account balance and get mini statements.\n\nRemember, never share your account number or any other sensitive information with unauthorized individuals to prevent fraud and unauthorized access to your account. If you suspect any misuse of your account information, contact SBI customer support immediately.\n\nIf you are trying to get information about someone else's account, note that doing so without proper authorization is illegal and unethical.",
